01:14.445 --> 01:18.709
OFF, BUT IF I HAD TO GUESS,

01:18.709 --> 01:22.553
I'D SAY IT HAS
A LOT TO DO WITH FEAR --

01:27.218 --> 01:29.490
FEAR OF REJECTION.

01:29.490 --> 01:31.692
â™ª SAVE ME â™ª

01:31.692 --> 01:34.165
â™ª SAVE ME â™ª

01:34.165 --> 01:36.367
WOULDN'T IT BE EASIER
TO JUST ASK HER OUT?

01:36.367 --> 01:38.429
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

01:38.429 --> 01:40.431
â™ª WHY WOULD I THINK
SUCH THINGS? â™ª

01:40.431 --> 01:43.534
â™ª CRAZY THOUGHTS HAVE
QUICK WINGS â™ª

01:43.534 --> 01:46.137
â™ª GAINING MOMENTUM FAST â™ª

01:46.137 --> 01:48.139
[ ALARM BUZZING ]

01:48.139 --> 01:50.811
â™ª ONE MINUTE, I AM FINE â™ª

01:50.811 --> 01:52.343
SHE'S GONNA BE LATE.

01:52.343 --> 01:54.415
MAYBE NOT.

01:54.415 --> 01:56.487
WE SHOULD WAIT FOR HER.

01:56.487 --> 01:57.648
DEFINITELY NOT.

01:57.648 --> 02:00.451
I'M NOT HER MOTHER,
AND YOU ARE NOT HER BOYFRIEND --

02:00.451 --> 02:01.822
NOT YET, ANYWAY.

02:01.822 --> 02:04.124
STOP, OKAY?
I TOLD YOU I'M NOT INTERESTED.

02:04.124 --> 02:05.896
LIFE IS SHORT, GEORGE.

02:05.896 --> 02:08.559
DO YOU REALLY WANT TO DIE
BEFORE YOU EVER ASK HER OUT?

02:08.559 --> 02:10.831
I DO NOT WANT
TO ASK HER OUT.

02:10.831 --> 02:13.464
DO YOU REALLY WANT
TO DIE A LIAR?

02:13.464 --> 02:16.437
I'M NOT --
I'M NOT DYING.

02:16.437 --> 02:20.571
SOMETIMES, THE FEAR IS JUST
OF MAKING A DECISION...

02:20.571 --> 02:22.873
â™ª SAVE ME â™ª

02:22.873 --> 02:24.675
...BECAUSE
WHAT IF YOU'RE WRONG?

02:24.675 --> 02:27.748
WHAT IF YOU'RE MAKING
A MISTAKE YOU CAN'T UNDO?

02:27.748 --> 02:30.281
CRAP.

02:30.281 --> 02:31.552
CRAP?

02:31.552 --> 02:32.923
HI. I'M LATE.

02:32.923 --> 02:34.825
YOU'RE AVOIDING ME.

02:34.825 --> 02:36.357
YES, BUT ALSO LATE.

02:36.357 --> 02:37.888
OH, ARE WE GONNA TALK
ABOUT THIS?

02:37.888 --> 02:39.190
NO.

02:39.190 --> 02:41.262
ABOUT US AND BAILEY
AND WHAT SHE SAW?

02:41.262 --> 02:43.634
I DON'T NEED TO TALK ABOUT IT.
I EXPERIENCED IT...

02:43.634 --> 02:44.665
NAKED.

02:44.665 --> 02:46.537
THIS IS GETTING
COMPLICATED.

02:46.537 --> 02:47.598
COMPLICATED FOR ME.

02:47.598 --> 02:49.540
I'M THE INTERN SLEEPING
WITH THE ATTENDING.

02:49.540 --> 02:51.772
BAILEY ISN'T SPEAKING
TO ME ANYMORE.

02:51.772 --> 02:53.604
NOT THAT THAT'S
A BAD THING.

02:53.604 --> 02:56.407
IF I WAS A BETTER GUY,
I'D WALK AWAY.

02:56.407 --> 02:57.778
YES, YOU WOULD.

02:57.778 --> 03:00.881
DO YOU WANT ME
TO BE A BETTER GUY?

03:00.881 --> 03:02.553
YES.

03:04.615 --> 03:06.557
NO.

03:06.557 --> 03:08.359
CRAP.

03:08.359 --> 03:09.960
I'M LATE.

03:09.960 --> 03:13.624
TAKE YOUR TIME.

03:13.624 --> 03:15.966
THINK ABOUT IT.

03:15.966 --> 03:17.498
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

03:17.498 --> 03:20.401
I REALLY NEEDED THAT.

03:20.401 --> 03:23.704
â™ª GIVE ME BACK MY... â™ª

03:23.704 --> 03:25.976
THANKS.

03:25.976 --> 03:28.679
â™ª ...SO WE'RE ALWAYS THE SAME â™ª

03:28.679 --> 03:31.912
IS THIS A --
SHOULD WE TALK ABOUT THIS?

03:31.912 --> 03:35.446
YEAH, DEFINITELY.

03:35.446 --> 03:37.618
â™ª SO WHERE YOU SLIP â™ª

03:37.618 --> 03:40.621
â™ª THAT IS THE WAY,
THAT IS THE WAY â™ª

03:46.857 --> 03:48.729
Grey:
YOU'RE LATE.

03:48.729 --> 03:50.331
SO ARE YOU.

03:50.331 --> 03:52.563
I KNOW, AND I CAN'T AFFORD
TO PISS OFF BAILEY ANY MORE.

03:52.563 --> 03:53.864
DO YOU THINK
SHE TOLD ANYONE?

03:53.864 --> 03:55.766
ABOUT YOU
AND McDREAMY? NO.

03:55.766 --> 03:57.708
HE'S HER BOSS, TOO.

03:57.708 --> 03:59.310
IF THEY FIND OUT,
WHAT CAN THEY --

03:59.310 --> 04:00.611
CAN THEY
KICK ME OUT, OR...

04:00.611 --> 04:02.713
NO...
NOT OFFICIALLY.

04:02.713 --> 04:07.247
YOU'LL JUST GET EDGED OUT,
BLACKLISTED,

04:07.247 --> 04:11.452
BANNED FROM HIS SURGERIES,
PASSED OVER FOR CHIEF RESIDENT.

04:11.452 --> 04:12.653
[ SIGHS ]

04:12.653 --> 04:14.685
IT'LL BE HUMILIATING,
BUT YOU'LL LIVE.

04:14.685 --> 04:18.959
I HAVE TO END IT.
I DEFINITELY HAVE TO END IT.

04:18.959 --> 04:21.692
I HAVE TO END IT,
RIGHT?

04:21.692 --> 04:23.734
MEREDITH, SHUT UP.

04:23.734 --> 04:25.296
WHAT?

04:25.296 --> 04:28.569
DID YOU SERIOUSLY
JUST TELL ME TO SHUT UP?

04:28.569 --> 04:29.600
OH, PLEASE.

04:29.600 --> 04:31.271
YOU GOT A HOT DOCTOR
WHO LIKES

04:31.271 --> 04:32.673
TO MAKE YOU OPEN UP
AND SAY "AHH."

04:32.673 --> 04:34.805
IT'S THE AMERICAN DREAM.
STOP WHINING ABOUT IT.

04:34.805 --> 04:37.478
NO. NO GOOD CAN COME FROM
SLEEPING WITH YOUR BOSS.

04:37.478 --> 04:38.649
CRISTINA,
YOU'RE LATE.

04:38.649 --> 04:40.050
SO IS MEREDITH.

04:40.050 --> 04:43.454
ONE THING HOLDS TRUE --

04:43.454 --> 04:45.716
IF, BY THE TIME THE PAIN
OF NOT DOING A THING

04:45.716 --> 04:47.818
GETS WORSE
THAN THE FEAR OF DOING IT,

04:47.818 --> 04:50.991
AROUND A GIANT TUMOR.

04:50.991 --> 04:53.724
WHEN WE WALK IN THIS DOOR,
YOU WILL MAINTAIN DECORUM.

04:53.724 --> 04:56.367
YOU WILL NOT LAUGH, VOMIT,
OR DROP YOUR JAW.

04:56.367 --> 04:57.768
ARE WE UNDERSTOOD?

04:57.768 --> 05:00.371
WHY WOULD WE LAUGH?
OH, JUST YOU WAIT.

05:00.371 --> 05:02.473
GOOD MORNING,
MISS CONNORS.

05:02.473 --> 05:04.605
Annie:
GOOD MORNING.

05:04.605 --> 05:08.038
WHAT IS IT?

05:08.038 --> 05:09.540
TUMOR.

05:09.540 --> 05:13.614
AND YOU THOUGHT

05:18.989 --> 05:22.893
â™ª NOBODY KNOWS
WHERE THEY MIGHT END UP â™ª

05:22.893 --> 05:26.056
â™ª NOBODY KNOWS â™ª

05:34.705 --> 05:39.940
â™ª OH, OH,
SUPPOSE YOU'LL NEVER KNOW â™ª

05:44.715 --> 05:46.847
GOOD MORNING, ANNIE.
HOW ARE YOU?

05:46.847 --> 05:49.450
THIS IS DR. BAILEY, AND
THESE ARE MY FELLOW INTERNS.

05:49.450 --> 05:51.522
DR. KAREV, WE REFER TO PATIENTS
AS "MISTER" --

05:51.522 --> 05:53.554
I TOLD HIM
TO CALL ME "ANNIE."

05:53.554 --> 05:55.956
"MS. CONNORS" MAKES ME FEEL
OLD AND FAT,

05:55.956 --> 05:59.760
WHICH I AM,
BUT WHY FEEL THAT WAY?

05:59.760 --> 06:01.762
Burke:
GOOD MORNING.

06:01.762 --> 06:04.765
OH, ANNIE, THIS IS DR. BURKE --
AWESOME SURGEON.

06:05.896 --> 06:07.468
DR. KAREV.

06:07.468 --> 06:10.771
OH, ANNIE CONNORS IS
A 43-YEAR-OLD WOMAN

06:10.771 --> 06:12.002
WHO PRESENTED LAST NIGHT

06:12.002 --> 06:13.844
WITH PROGRESSIVE
SHORTNESS OF BREATH

06:13.844 --> 06:14.905
FOR THE PAST THREE MONTHS.

06:14.905 --> 06:18.879
FOUND TO HAVE A VERY LARGE TUMOR
OF UNKNOWN ORIGIN

06:18.879 --> 06:20.581
PRESSED AGAINST
HER DIAPHRAGM.

06:20.581 --> 06:21.682
STABLE VITAL SIGNS.

06:21.682 --> 06:23.784
SCHEDULED FOR C.T.
THIS MORNING, SIR.

06:23.784 --> 06:26.717
THANK YOU, DR. KAREV.
ARE YOU AT ALL CLAUSTROPHOBIC?

06:26.717 --> 06:28.889
Annie: I'VE BEEN HOUSEBOUND
FOR THE LAST YEAR.

06:28.889 --> 06:30.791
HOW CLAUSTROPHOBIC
COULD I BE?

06:30.791 --> 06:32.863
ALL RIGHT, THEN.

06:32.863 --> 06:35.065
DR. STEVENS IS GOING
TO TAKE YOU UP FOR A C.T.

06:35.065 --> 06:36.897
IT'LL GIVE US A BETTER LOOK
AT THE TUMOR,

06:36.897 --> 06:38.599
AND WE'LL KNOW
HOW TO PROCEED.

06:38.599 --> 06:40.070
COULD SOMEONE TELL MY MOM?

06:40.070 --> 06:42.633
SHE'LL WORRY IF SHE GETS BACK
AND I'M NOT HERE.

06:42.633 --> 06:45.476
YEAH, OF COURSE.
OF COURSE.

06:45.476 --> 06:48.639
AND WOULD IT BE POSSIBLE
FOR ALEX TO TAKE ME INSTEAD?

06:48.639 --> 06:52.943
I MEAN, HE -- HE'S JUST
SO FUN TO LOOK AT.

06:52.943 --> 06:55.115
[ CHUCKLING ]
ANNIE.

06:55.115 --> 06:57.788
SURE.
SURE, MS. CONNORS.

06:57.788 --> 07:00.050
EXCUSE ME.

07:01.421 --> 07:03.694
HOW MUCH
DO YOU THINK IT WEIGHS?

07:03.694 --> 07:04.895
60 POUNDS.

07:04.895 --> 07:06.827
SHE'S CARRYING AROUND
A WHOLE EXTRA PERSON.

07:06.827 --> 07:08.859
THIS ONE'S GOING IN THE BOOKS.
I'VE GOT TO GET IN.

07:08.859 --> 07:10.100
I ALMOST DID.

07:10.100 --> 07:11.732
HAVE YOU EVER SEEN ALEX
LIKE THAT?

07:11.732 --> 07:12.963
HE ACTUALLY SEEMED SINCERE.

07:12.963 --> 07:14.705
"SEEMED" BEING
THE OPERATIVE WORD.

07:14.705 --> 07:15.966
HE WAS ON CALL
WHEN SHE CAME IN.

07:15.966 --> 07:17.768
I AM NEVER LEAVING
THIS PLACE AGAIN.

07:17.768 --> 07:19.870
LET'S MOVE, PEOPLE.

07:19.870 --> 07:22.773
MS. CONNOR'S SURGERY,
SHOULD WE CHOOSE TO PROCEED,

07:22.773 --> 07:25.546
WILL TAKE MOST, IF NOT ALL,
OF THE SURGEONS OFF THE FLOOR,

07:25.546 --> 07:26.777
WHICH MEANS YOU PEOPLE

07:26.777 --> 07:29.119
WILL HAVE TO WORK EXTRA HARD
NOT TO KILL ANYONE,

07:29.119 --> 07:31.852
'CAUSE WE WON'T BE THERE
TO FIX YOUR MISTAKES.

07:31.852 --> 07:33.524
DR. BURKE.

07:33.524 --> 07:36.757
Woman on P.A.:
TRAUMA TEAM TO O.R. 1.
TRAUMA TEAM TO O.R. 1.

07:36.757 --> 07:37.958
I REALLY WANT IN
ON THIS.

07:37.958 --> 07:39.830
I THOUGHT
WE WEREN'T TALKING.

07:39.830 --> 07:42.092
I'M NOT TALKING.
I'M JUST SAYING.

07:42.092 --> 07:43.664
[ SIGHS ]

07:43.664 --> 07:47.538
FIND HER MOTHER, GET A FAMILY
HISTORY, AND I'LL TELL BAILEY.

07:49.900 --> 07:52.543
MR. HARPER HAD
A CORONARY BYPASS YESTERDAY.

07:52.543 --> 07:54.905
HIS BLOOD PRESSURE,
CURRENTLY 100/65.

07:54.905 --> 07:57.878
IT WAS RUNNING LOW OVERNIGHT
DOWN TO 70/30,

07:57.878 --> 07:59.950
BUT RESPONDED TO MEDICATION.

07:59.950 --> 08:03.253
POSTOPERATIVE LABS SHOW A CRIT
OF 30 AND NORMAL COAGULATION.

08:03.253 --> 08:05.916
CHEST-TUBE OUTPUT HAS HALTED
OVER THE LAST TWO HOURS.

08:05.916 --> 08:07.688
WHAT'S YOUR PLAN?

08:07.688 --> 08:10.661
CHEST X-RAY AND CHECK THE TUBE
FOR POSSIBLE OCCLUSION.

08:10.661 --> 08:12.492
GOOD.
HE'S DOING FINE.

08:12.492 --> 08:14.825
THANK YOU.

08:23.834 --> 08:25.536
I KNOW YOU THINK
I LIKE MEREDITH,

08:25.536 --> 08:26.937
BUT I DON'T LIKE
MEREDITH.

08:26.937 --> 08:27.938
WHAT?

08:27.938 --> 08:30.541
NO. I LIKE MEREDITH.
OBVIOUSLY, I LIKE MEREDITH.

08:30.541 --> 08:32.543
I JUST -- I JUST DON'T HAVE
A THING FOR HER.

08:32.543 --> 08:33.944
OKAY.

08:33.944 --> 08:36.917
IT'S JUST THIS MORNING -- I KNOW
YOU WERE PROBABLY JUST TEASING,

08:36.917 --> 08:39.049
BUT I DON'T WANT YOU TO SAY
ANYTHING LIKE THAT TO HER,

08:39.049 --> 08:41.752
BECAUSE WE LIVE TOGETHER, AND
THAT WOULD BE REALLY AWKWARD.

08:41.752 --> 08:42.893
GEORGE, STOP TALKING.

08:42.893 --> 08:45.155
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

08:47.898 --> 08:49.760
MORNING.

08:49.760 --> 08:53.003
MR. LEVANGIE,
THIS IS DR. BAILEY

08:53.003 --> 08:55.265
AND HER FINE STAFF
OF SURGICAL INTERNS.

09:00.871 --> 09:02.973
WELCOME TO HELL, KIDS.

09:02.973 --> 09:04.775
[ GROANING ]

09:04.775 --> 09:06.216
WHO'S PRESENTING?

09:06.216 --> 09:09.149
EDWARD LEVANGIE IS
A 63-YEAR-OLD MAN ADMITTED

09:09.149 --> 09:11.051
FOR PAIN MANAGEMENT
FOR DYSKINESIA.

09:11.051 --> 09:13.223
HE'S BEEN STABLE
SINCE LAST NIGHT

09:13.223 --> 09:15.285
AND RESPONDING WELL
TO THE BOLUS INJECTIONS.

09:15.285 --> 09:16.957
IZZIE,
POSSIBLE TREATMENTS?

09:16.957 --> 09:18.829
Stevens:
FOR PARKINSON'S DISEASE?

09:18.829 --> 09:20.861
DEEP BRAIN STIMULATION
HAS SHOWN VERY --

09:20.861 --> 09:22.793
NOT FOR PARKINSON'S --
FOR SPINAL PAIN.

09:22.793 --> 09:25.235
OH, UM...

09:25.235 --> 09:27.998
INTRASPINAL CATHETER --

09:27.998 --> 09:30.771
THAT WAY, HE CAN HAVE
CONSTANT PAIN MEDICATION.

09:30.771 --> 09:33.303
EXCELLENT.
THIS IS DR. GREY.

09:33.303 --> 09:36.006
SHE'S GONNA PREP YOU
FOR THE PROCEDURE AND ASSIST.

09:36.907 --> 09:39.950
[ PAGER BEEPS ]

09:39.950 --> 09:41.581
EXCUSE ME.

09:45.015 --> 09:48.819
YOU MAKE YOURSELVES BUSY.
I'LL CATCH UP WITH YOU.

09:58.929 --> 10:01.271
Woman:
I'LL SEE YOU OVER THERE.

10:05.005 --> 10:06.606
MIRANDA.

10:06.606 --> 10:07.938
EXCUSE ME?

10:07.938 --> 10:10.180
WELL, THAT'S YOUR NAME, RIGHT?
IT'S ON YOUR JACKET.

10:10.180 --> 10:12.643
ALL RIGHT, FINE, I'LL
JUST CALL YOU "BAILEY" THEN.

10:12.643 --> 10:14.915
YOU THINK YOU'RE CHARMING
IN THAT TALENTED, NEUROTIC,

10:14.915 --> 10:16.717
OVERLY MOUSSED HAIR
SORT OF WAY.

10:16.717 --> 10:18.048
GOOD FOR YOU.

10:18.048 --> 10:19.750
BUT IF YOU THINK
I'M GONNA STAND BACK

10:19.750 --> 10:21.051
AND WATCH
WHILE YOU FAVOR HER --

10:21.051 --> 10:22.853
I DON'T FAVOR HER.
SHE'S GOOD.

10:22.853 --> 10:23.954
I'M SURE SHE IS.

10:23.954 --> 10:26.797
CAN I POINT OUT THAT,
TECHNICALLY, I'M YOUR BOSS?

10:26.797 --> 10:27.998
YOU DON'T SCARE ME.

10:27.998 --> 10:30.030
LOOK, I'M NOT
GONNA ADVERTISE

10:30.030 --> 10:32.803
YOUR EXTRACURRICULAR ACTIVITIES
WITH MY INTERN.

10:32.803 --> 10:35.135
HOWEVER, THE NEXT TIME I SEE YOU
FAVORING MEREDITH GREY

10:35.135 --> 10:37.267
IN ANY WAY, I'LL MAKE SURE
SHE DOESN'T SEE

10:37.267 --> 10:40.140
THE INSIDE OF AN O.R.
FOR A MONTH...

10:40.140 --> 10:42.312
JUST FOR THE SAKE
OF BALANCE.

10:42.312 --> 10:44.975
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

10:44.975 --> 10:47.277
WE'RE ALL SET, DOC.
OKAY.

10:47.277 --> 10:50.280
ANNIE...THERE'S GONNA BE
A MICROPHONE IN THERE FOR YOU

10:50.280 --> 10:51.852
IN CASE YOU GET SCARED

10:51.852 --> 10:54.654
OR YOU WANT TO GET OUT,
BUT TRY NOT TO DO THAT,

10:54.654 --> 10:57.728
BECAUSE THEN WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO
START ALL OVER AGAIN.

10:57.728 --> 10:59.289
I'M FINE.
I'LL BE FINE.

10:59.289 --> 11:02.032
I KNOW YOU'RE GONNA BE FINE,
BECAUSE I'M GONNA BE

11:02.032 --> 11:05.395
RIGHT OVER THERE, BEHIND
THAT GLASS, WAITING FOR YOU.

11:05.395 --> 11:07.137
ALL RIGHT?
OKAY.

11:07.137 --> 11:08.799
YOU READY?

11:08.799 --> 11:11.301
ARE YOU REALLY READY?
LET'S DO THIS.

11:11.301 --> 11:13.944
SEE YA.

11:20.010 --> 11:22.783
OH, HEY, MAN,
YOU GOT AN EXTRA BATTERY?

11:22.783 --> 11:26.116
UNBELIEVABLE.

11:26.116 --> 11:27.818
OH, I KNOW, RIGHT?

11:27.818 --> 11:29.289
I'VE NEVER SEEN
ANYTHING LIKE THIS.

11:29.289 --> 11:30.690
GOD.

11:30.690 --> 11:32.462
YEAH, WELL,
WHAT I DON'T UNDERSTAND

11:32.462 --> 11:34.694
is how a person
lets it get like that.

11:34.694 --> 11:38.028
I mean, man,
that is a whole lot of nasty.

11:38.028 --> 11:41.001
Maybe she's afraid of doctors.
Poor thing.

11:41.001 --> 11:42.702
Poor thing? Please.

11:42.702 --> 11:44.805
If you're afraid of doctors,
you take a pill.

11:44.805 --> 11:48.038
She's just sick,
like, warped, you know?

11:48.038 --> 11:51.311
Seriously, I don't know
how she lives with herself.

11:51.311 --> 11:53.483
[ Laughing ]
Ugh.

11:59.049 --> 12:01.752
WELL, AT FIRST, WE THOUGHT
SHE WAS JUST PUTTING ON WEIGHT.

12:01.752 --> 12:03.453
WHEN WE REALIZED
WHAT WAS HAPPENING,

12:03.453 --> 12:08.098
I TRIED TO GET HER TO GO TO
THE DOCTOR, BUT SHE WAS SCARED.

12:08.098 --> 12:11.031
AND THE BIGGER IT GOT,
THE LESS SHE WANTED TO GO.

12:11.031 --> 12:15.335
AND SHE NEVER REALLY FELT
ALL THAT SICK UNTIL LAST NIGHT.

12:15.335 --> 12:17.207
SHE COULDN'T BREATHE.

12:17.207 --> 12:20.010
