25:30.660 --> 25:32.702
SO, NO, DR. GREY,

25:32.702 --> 25:35.965
I DON'T CARE WHAT YOU KNEW
OR WHEN YOU KNEW IT.

25:35.965 --> 25:38.267
ARE WE UNDERSTOOD?

25:38.267 --> 25:40.169
YES.
GOOD.

25:56.055 --> 25:57.587
Karev:
THIS SUCKS.

25:57.587 --> 26:00.129
YEAH, WELL, I'M NOT A REAL FAN
OF YOURS, EITHER.

26:00.129 --> 26:01.861
NOT YOU -- THIS -- EVERYONE ELSE
IS SCRUBBED IN SOMEWHERE.

26:01.861 --> 26:03.863
BRIGHT SIDE --
WE HAVE THE RUN OF THE FLOOR.

26:03.863 --> 26:05.134
WANT TO DO IT
IN THE STAIRWELL?

26:05.134 --> 26:07.637
I'M JUST SAYING YOU NEVER KNOW
WHAT COULD HAPPEN.

26:09.338 --> 26:10.970
OOPS.

26:10.970 --> 26:12.141
I'M CHANGING.

26:12.141 --> 26:13.903
I'LL PAGE YOU
IF I NEED YOU.

26:13.903 --> 26:17.076
YOU DO THAT.

26:17.076 --> 26:19.609
YOU ARE SO
MY FAVORITE PERSON TODAY.

26:22.181 --> 26:23.683
BEGIN MORE SUCTION.

26:23.683 --> 26:27.857
WE NEED TO HANG
ANOTHER BAG OF O-NEG.

26:27.857 --> 26:31.260
CAUTERIZING THE SMALL BLEEDERS
TO KEEP MY VISUAL FIELD CLEAN.

26:31.260 --> 26:32.892
GOD, IS YOUR BACK
KILLING YOU?

26:32.892 --> 26:34.624
GEORGE, SHUT UP.
WE'RE IN HERE.

26:34.624 --> 26:36.025
MORE SUCTION, PLEASE.

26:36.025 --> 26:38.628
OKAY, HOLD IT RIGHT THERE.

26:42.371 --> 26:46.035
MRS. HARPER, LET ME SHOW YOU
THESE CHEST FILMS.

26:46.035 --> 26:48.878
WE WERE ABLE TO RELIEVE THE
OBSTRUCTION OF HIS CHEST TUBE,

26:48.878 --> 26:52.011
SO THE BUILDUP OF FLUID YOU SEE
HERE SHOULD RESOLVE ITSELF SOON.

26:55.084 --> 26:57.947
WHICH TRANSLATES
AS HE SHOULD BE HOME IN NO TIME.

26:57.947 --> 26:59.889
HE WAS MAKING WAFFLES.

26:59.889 --> 27:00.920
I'M SORRY?

27:00.920 --> 27:02.291
HE WAS MAKING WAFFLES.

27:02.291 --> 27:06.125
HE WAS MIXING THE BATTER, AND --
AND THEN, HE WAS ON THE FLOOR.

27:06.125 --> 27:08.227
IZZIE, WE NEED
A CENTRAL LINE RUN IN 204.

27:08.227 --> 27:10.299
PAGE DR. KAREV, WILL YOU?
HE'S NOT ANSWERING.

27:10.299 --> 27:13.362
[ SIGHS ] I'M SO SORRY.
I'LL BE BACK.

27:15.264 --> 27:18.007
[ PAGER BEEPING ]

27:24.944 --> 27:26.716
LIKE WHAT YOU SEE,
RIGHT?

27:32.982 --> 27:35.084
Woman:
NEURO SPONGE.

27:35.084 --> 27:38.057
HOW YOU DOING,
MR. LEVANGIE?

27:38.057 --> 27:40.059
ALL RIGHT.

27:40.059 --> 27:41.931
WHERE'S BLONDIE?

27:41.931 --> 27:43.963
I'M RIGHT HERE.
CAN'T YOU SEE ME?

27:43.963 --> 27:46.665
I'M SHAKY.
I'M NOT BLIND.

27:46.665 --> 27:49.739
ANYTHING GOES WRONG HERE,
I'M BLAMING YOU.

27:49.739 --> 27:53.242
OKAY, IN THAT CASE, I'LL STAY
WHERE YOU CAN SEE ME.

27:53.242 --> 27:55.745
Woman: WE JUST HAVE TO DRILL
A HOLE AND TRY TO FIND

27:55.745 --> 27:58.347
THE SPOT THAT CONTROLS
THE MOTOR FUNCTION.

27:58.347 --> 28:00.679
YOU CAN'T SEE MY BRAIN
FROM THERE.

28:00.679 --> 28:02.912
AREN'T YOU SUPPOSED
TO BE LEARNING SOMETHING?

28:02.912 --> 28:07.086
I'M GOOD RIGHT HERE.

28:07.086 --> 28:10.760
OKAY, MR. LEVANGIE, JUST
TAKE A COUPLE DEEP BREATHS.

28:10.760 --> 28:13.162
FOCUS ON THE PRETTY GIRL.
[ WHIRRING ]

28:13.162 --> 28:16.225
OKAY, THIS IS GONNA SOUND REALLY
SCARY, BUT TRY AND RELAX.

28:16.225 --> 28:17.867
YOU SHOULDN'T FEEL
A THING.

28:19.098 --> 28:21.170
ANY PAIN HERE?
HERE?

28:21.170 --> 28:23.132
[ PAGER BEEPING ]
OKAY.

28:23.132 --> 28:26.475
DR. STEVENS, I NEED YOU
TO CHECK THE X-RAY IN 2103.

28:26.475 --> 28:29.138
2118 NEEDS POST-OP NOTES,
AND JANE'S WONDERING

28:29.138 --> 28:31.080
IF YOU WANT HER
TO START FEEDING 2112.

28:31.080 --> 28:32.341
I'M GOING ON BREAK.

28:32.341 --> 28:35.414
OKAY, YEAH, BEFORE YOU DO THAT,
COULD YOU PAGE DR. KAREV AGAIN?

28:35.414 --> 28:37.116
I ALREADY PAGED HIM.
YEAH, AGAIN?

28:41.050 --> 28:42.892
HOW IS IT?

28:42.892 --> 28:45.494
LONG AND SLOW.
I DON'T ENVY THOSE TWO.

28:45.494 --> 28:48.397
THEY'VE BEEN HOLDING THAT THING
FOR EIGHT HOURS.

28:48.397 --> 28:51.801
THEIR ARMS HAVE TO BE READY
TO FALL OFF.

28:51.801 --> 28:55.464
Burke: LOOK AT THE SIZE
OF THIS ARTERY.

28:55.464 --> 28:58.437
MY GOD.
IT'S AS THICK AS A THUMB.

28:58.437 --> 29:01.440
YOU EVER SEEN A VESSEL
THIS SIZE?

29:01.440 --> 29:03.773
NO.

29:03.773 --> 29:08.377
THIS THING'S JUST FEEDING
ON ALL HER BLOOD.

29:08.377 --> 29:10.749
WE NEED MORE O-NEGATIVE.

29:10.749 --> 29:12.822
I'LL CALL
THE BLOOD BANK.

29:12.822 --> 29:15.324
DAMN IT, O'MALLEY.

29:15.324 --> 29:18.027
DO YOU WANT ME
TO KILL THIS PATIENT?!

29:18.027 --> 29:19.358
NO, I -- SORRY.

29:19.358 --> 29:22.061
I MEAN, IS THE ART OF RETRACTING
JUST TOO MUCH FOR YOU?

29:22.061 --> 29:23.933
NO, I WAS, UH --

29:23.933 --> 29:26.335
UM...

29:26.335 --> 29:28.437
I HAD AN ITCH.

29:30.099 --> 29:32.271
WAY TO GO, GEORGE.
NICELY DONE.

29:34.243 --> 29:37.406
JUST KEEP TRYING, MR. LEVANGIE.
MIMIC MY MOTIONS.

29:37.406 --> 29:40.549
YOU CAN DO IT.

29:40.549 --> 29:42.551
YOU'RE DOING GREAT,
MR. LEVANGIE.

29:42.551 --> 29:44.083
JUST A LITTLE LONGER.

29:44.083 --> 29:45.454
OH, DAMN IT!

29:46.856 --> 29:50.119
TAKE A BREATH
AND TRY AGAIN.

29:50.119 --> 29:52.421
ONE MORE TIME,
MR. LEVANGIE.

29:52.421 --> 29:54.393
THE PROBE IS ALMOST IN.

29:54.393 --> 29:57.196
YOU'LL KNOW IT
WHEN WE FIND THE RIGHT SPOT.

30:08.307 --> 30:10.109
WELL, HOW ABOUT THAT?

30:10.109 --> 30:12.181
Shepherd:
THERE IT IS.

30:12.181 --> 30:15.184
I'LL BE A SON OF A BITCH.

30:23.893 --> 30:25.995
I WAS TRYING
TO PROTECT YOU.

30:25.995 --> 30:29.198
YOU TRYING TO PROTECT ME IS
WHY SHE'S ON THE WARPATH.

30:29.198 --> 30:31.060
YOU CAN'T DO ME FAVORS.

30:31.060 --> 30:34.233
YOU CAN'T ASK ME TO SCRUB IN
WHEN I HAVEN'T EARNED IT.

30:34.233 --> 30:37.136
AND YOU CAN'T TREAT ME LIKE CRAP
WHEN I HAVEN'T EARNED THAT.

30:37.136 --> 30:38.607
I CAN TAKE CARE
OF MYSELF.

30:38.607 --> 30:41.010
I GOT MYSELF INTO THIS MESS,
AND I...

30:41.010 --> 30:42.872
AND YOU'LL
GET YOURSELF OUT?

30:42.872 --> 30:45.444
I DON'T...
KNOW THAT YET.

30:45.444 --> 30:47.216
[ PAGER BEEPING ]

30:49.278 --> 30:52.021
DON'T LET ME KEEP YOU.

30:52.021 --> 30:54.924
YOU DID
GREAT WORK HERE TODAY.

30:54.924 --> 30:58.157
DR. SHEPHERD.

30:58.157 --> 30:59.358
YEAH?

30:59.358 --> 31:01.931
SORRY I CALLED YOU
A JACKASS.

31:01.931 --> 31:03.192
YOU DIDN'T.

31:03.192 --> 31:06.295
I DID...TWICE.

31:08.237 --> 31:12.241
TELL YOU WHAT, BLONDIE, IF
YOU DON'T MARRY HIM, I WILL.

31:18.507 --> 31:20.209
[ PAGER BEEPING ]

31:27.656 --> 31:30.960
NO, NO, NO, JIMMY!
NO, NO, JIMMY, NO!

31:30.960 --> 31:32.161
WHAT WE GOT?

31:32.161 --> 31:34.163
PRESSURE PLUMMETED
TO 64/22,

31:34.163 --> 31:36.295
AND HE HAS RUNS OF V-TACH
THAT AREN'T PERFUSING.

31:36.295 --> 31:37.526
CVP IS SKY-HIGH.

31:37.526 --> 31:39.328
GIVE HIM DOPAMINE --
10 MIKES.

31:39.328 --> 31:40.629
HE'S ALREADY MAXED OUT.

31:40.629 --> 31:43.933
THE RESIDENT WAS HERE AN HOUR
AGO, BUT I CAN'T REACH HIM NOW.

31:43.933 --> 31:45.404
WHAT IS THE MATTER
WITH YOU?!

31:45.404 --> 31:47.506
GET HER OUT OF HERE!

31:47.506 --> 31:49.979
MRS. HARPER,
YOU HAVE TO GET OUT OF HERE.

31:49.979 --> 31:52.982
DOES HE HAVE
A MYOCARDIAL ISCHEMIA?

31:52.982 --> 31:54.343
NO, IT'S A CLOT --
BIG ONE.

31:54.343 --> 31:56.345
PAGE SOMEONE.
PAGE ANYONE.

31:56.345 --> 31:58.447
HE'LL BE DEAD
BEFORE THEY GET HERE.

31:58.447 --> 32:02.121
DO ANYTHING, PLEASE!
YOU SAID HE WAS OKAY!

32:02.121 --> 32:03.192
GET OUT OF HERE NOW!

32:03.192 --> 32:04.423
YOU HAVE TO CUT.

32:04.423 --> 32:06.025
I CAN'T.

32:06.025 --> 32:08.257
I'VE NEVER EVEN SEEN IT DONE.
I COULD KILL HIM.

32:08.257 --> 32:09.658
DO NOTHING,
YOU'LL KILL HIM FASTER.

32:09.658 --> 32:11.130
WHAT'S YOUR GLOVE SIZE?
6.

32:11.130 --> 32:13.162
OH, GOD.
OH, GOD.

32:13.162 --> 32:14.703
TAKE A BREATH,
DR. STEVENS.

32:14.703 --> 32:16.205
SHE HAS TO MOVE
OVER THERE.

32:16.205 --> 32:17.406
WALTER, MOVE OUT
OF THE WAY.

32:20.209 --> 32:24.013
CUT THE STITCHES
AND THEN THE STAPLES.

32:24.013 --> 32:26.345
DON'T LET THEM FALL
INTO THE CHEST CAVITY.

32:26.345 --> 32:29.148
WAIT. I'VE NEVER CRACKED
A CHEST BEFORE.

32:29.148 --> 32:32.381
OH, GOD.
OH, GOD.

32:39.128 --> 32:41.060
NO PULSE.
WIDE COMPLEX RHYTHM.

32:41.060 --> 32:44.033
I CAN'T GET THIS CLOT OUT.
I NEED MORE SUCTION.

32:44.033 --> 32:45.434
HE'S BRADYING DOWN.

32:45.434 --> 32:48.297
YOU HAVE TO GET
THE CLOT OUT.

32:48.297 --> 32:50.039
I CAN'T GET IT.

32:50.039 --> 32:53.042
SCREW IT.
I'M USING MY HAND.

32:55.344 --> 32:58.207
OH, GOD, LOOK AT
THE SIZE OF THAT CLOT.

32:59.478 --> 33:00.509
ANYTHING?

33:00.509 --> 33:02.011
NO.

33:02.011 --> 33:04.253
YOU HAVE TO MASSAGE
THE HEART, DOCTOR.

33:08.117 --> 33:11.590
COME ON.
COME ON.

33:13.292 --> 33:16.325
COME ON, PLEASE.

33:16.325 --> 33:19.198
COME ON, MR. HARPER.

33:19.198 --> 33:21.100
WE HAVE A PULSE.

33:21.100 --> 33:23.772
[ PANTING ]

33:30.379 --> 33:32.141
OKAY, MORE SUCTION.

33:32.141 --> 33:34.043
HOW'S IT GOING?

33:34.043 --> 33:37.186
IT'S MORE INTERTWINED THAN
THE STUDIES MADE IT LOOK.

33:37.186 --> 33:39.518
I NEED ANOTHER BAG.
CALL THE BLOOD BANK.

33:39.518 --> 33:41.220
WE NEED MORE O-NEGATIVE.

33:41.220 --> 33:44.193
I'M DOWN 10 UNITS OF BLOOD, AND
I HAVEN'T EVEN FLIPPED HER YET.

33:44.193 --> 33:45.224
OH, WOW.

33:45.224 --> 33:47.226
HMM.

33:47.226 --> 33:48.327
HOLD IT STEADY.

33:48.327 --> 33:50.199
LOOK AT THAT.

33:50.199 --> 33:51.230
SPONGE.

33:53.132 --> 33:55.404
NOW, HOW AM I SUPPOSED TO GET
AROUND THAT ARTERY?

33:55.404 --> 33:57.366
LET ME CALL DOWN
AND SEE...

33:57.366 --> 34:00.309
OKAY.

34:00.309 --> 34:03.312
ALL RIGHT, THEN.
FORCEPS.

34:03.312 --> 34:05.274
HERE YOU GO.

34:07.416 --> 34:09.378
EXCUSE ME.

34:09.378 --> 34:11.150
GOD, IT'S UNBELIEVABLE.

34:11.150 --> 34:12.381
RIGHT.

34:12.381 --> 34:14.723
HOW DID SHE LIVE
LIKE THAT?

34:14.723 --> 34:18.257
WATCH WHAT YOU SAY.
YOU NEVER KNOW WHO'S LISTENING.

34:18.257 --> 34:19.328
[ LAUGHING ]

34:19.328 --> 34:20.829
LOOK AT GEORGE.

34:20.829 --> 34:23.392
HE LOOKS LIKE
HE'S ABOUT TO FALL IN.

34:23.392 --> 34:27.836
ARE YOU REALLY AS SHALLOW
AND CALLOUS AS YOU SEEM?

34:27.836 --> 34:30.799
OH, YOU WANT TO GO OUT
FOR A DRINK LATER

34:30.799 --> 34:33.342
AND HEAR ABOUT
MY SECRET PAIN?

34:33.342 --> 34:35.244
DOES THAT LINE
EVER WORK FOR YOU?

34:35.244 --> 34:36.375
SOMETIMES.

34:36.375 --> 34:38.447
OH.

34:38.447 --> 34:40.479
MUST BE BECAUSE
YOU LOOK LIKE THAT.

34:40.479 --> 34:41.750
LIKE WHAT?

34:43.352 --> 34:45.584
[ CHUCKLING ]
SO, IS THAT A YES?

34:45.584 --> 34:47.656
NO.

34:47.656 --> 34:50.589
I CAN'T.
I'M SEEING SOMEONE.

34:50.589 --> 34:53.462
LOOK, IF YOU DON'T WANT
TO GO OUT WITH ME,

34:53.462 --> 34:55.324
JUST SAY SO --
NO NEED TO LIE.

34:55.324 --> 34:58.167
OH, OKAY.

34:58.167 --> 35:00.529
WELL, I DON'T WANT
TO GO OUT WITH YOU.

35:00.529 --> 35:04.203
BUT I THINK I REALLY
MIGHT BE SEEING SOMEONE.

35:04.203 --> 35:06.305
YEAH.
NO, IT'S UP HERE.

35:06.305 --> 35:08.177
IT'S UP HERE.
IT'S UP HERE.

35:08.177 --> 35:10.479
WE'RE STILL IN
THE MIDDLE OF SURGERY.

35:10.479 --> 35:13.482
MR. HARPER, THE POST-OP HEART
PATIENT IN 2114 --

35:13.482 --> 35:15.684
I HAD TO OPEN
HIS STERNOTOMY BEDSIDE.

35:15.684 --> 35:16.785
YOU WHAT?

35:16.785 --> 35:17.786
WHAT?

35:17.786 --> 35:19.418
WHAT?

35:19.418 --> 35:21.590
HE HAD CARDIAC TAMPONADE.

35:21.590 --> 35:23.422
HIS CHEST FILMS WERE CLEAN
THIS MORNING.

35:23.422 --> 35:24.423
IT HAPPENED FAST.

35:24.423 --> 35:26.325
HE WAS IN P.E.A.
THERE WAS NO TIME.

35:28.457 --> 35:30.629
GO AHEAD.
I GOT IT.

35:30.629 --> 35:32.261
WE'RE OKAY HERE.

35:32.261 --> 35:33.532
YEAH,
I NEED SOME RETRACTION.

35:33.532 --> 35:35.464
PULL BACK ON THE RETRACTOR.
I GOT IT.

35:36.335 --> 35:39.238
YOU OPENED A HEART BEDSIDE,
AND YOU COULDN'T EVEN PAGE ME?

35:39.238 --> 35:41.670
NEEDED ALL THE GLORY
FOR YOURSELF, RIGHT?

35:41.670 --> 35:43.242
I PAGED YOU 50 TIMES.

35:43.242 --> 35:46.345
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT I HAVE BEEN THROUGH?

35:46.345 --> 35:47.446
OH, MAN.

35:47.446 --> 35:49.718
THE BATTERY --
I FORGOT TO CHANGE IT.

35:49.718 --> 35:51.380
YOU FORGOT?

35:51.380 --> 35:52.521
YOU FORGOT?!

35:52.521 --> 35:53.852
YOU ARE HATEFUL!

35:53.852 --> 35:57.926
YOU ARE A HATEFUL, LAZY,
ARROGANT, HATEFUL MAN!

35:59.258 --> 36:00.589
HATEFUL!

36:00.589 --> 36:02.691
NEVER A DULL MOMENT
HERE AT SEATTLE GRACE.

36:02.691 --> 36:04.693
OH!
OH, MY GOD.

36:04.693 --> 36:06.235
GET RIGHT IN THERE.
GET IT.

36:06.235 --> 36:08.197
SHE CAN'T AFFORD
TO LOSE THIS MUCH BLOOD.

36:08.197 --> 36:10.869
GET ME SOME SUCTION HERE.
I CAN'T SEE WHAT I'M DOING.

36:10.869 --> 36:12.541
CLAMP, CLAMP, CLAMP,
PLEASE.

36:20.849 --> 36:23.382
IS THERE ANY BLOOD
IN THE RAPID INFUSER?

36:23.382 --> 36:23.482
WE'RE WAITING ON TWO UNITS.

36:23.482 --> 36:25.183
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU'RE WAITING?

36:25.183 --> 36:26.855
WE DIDN'T ANTICIPATE
THIS MUCH BLOOD LOSS.

36:26.855 --> 36:29.358
WE PREPPED A DOUBLE SUPPLY.
WE'VE USED IT ALL.

36:29.358 --> 36:31.360
WHAT DID YOU CUT?
NOTHING.
IT JUST BLEW.

36:31.360 --> 36:33.922
SHE CAME IN
WITH TOO MUCH DAMAGE.

36:33.922 --> 36:35.464
THE ARTERY WALLS
ARE TOO WEAK.

36:35.464 --> 36:36.465
TAKE CARE OF IT.

36:36.465 --> 36:37.966
ANNIE, COME ON.

36:37.966 --> 36:39.197
10 UNITS OF O-NEGATIVE.

36:39.197 --> 36:40.429
I CANNOT SEE --
WHAT'S THIS?

36:40.429 --> 36:43.672
GEORGE, GIVE ME YOUR HAND.
PUSH RIGHT DOWN HERE. PULL.

36:43.672 --> 36:44.603
SUCTION, SUCTION!

36:44.603 --> 36:46.405
THE PRESSURE'S DROPPING.

36:46.405 --> 36:47.706
WHERE THE HELL
IS THE BLOOD?!

36:51.680 --> 36:53.742
SOMEBODY GRAB THAT.
PUSH IT BACK, GEORGE.

36:53.742 --> 36:54.943
COME ON.

36:58.387 --> 37:00.549
OH, GOD. JUST SQUEEZE IT OFF
RIGHT THERE.

37:00.549 --> 37:02.491
HERE WE GO.

37:07.326 --> 37:09.328
IS THAT O-NEGATIVE
FOR O.R. 1?

37:09.328 --> 37:10.329
UH-HUH, O.R. 1.

37:10.329 --> 37:11.330
O.R. 1, RIGHT?

37:11.330 --> 37:12.731
I GOT IT!
I GOT IT!

37:15.734 --> 37:17.566
SOME SUCTION, PLEASE,
IN HERE, NOW.

37:17.566 --> 37:18.667
[ FLATLINING ]

37:18.667 --> 37:20.409
OH, CHRIST,
WE'RE LOSING HER NOW.

37:20.409 --> 37:22.911
LOOK AT THIS.
COME ON.

37:22.911 --> 37:25.274
[ FLATLINING CONTINUES ]

37:37.426 --> 37:39.588
OH, COME ON!

37:39.588 --> 37:40.989
COME ON!

37:40.989 --> 37:44.893
[ GRUNTING ]

37:52.401 --> 37:54.703
[ PANTING ]

38:00.809 --> 38:03.382
[ MONITOR SWITCHES OFF ]

38:10.419 --> 38:13.592
TIME OF DEATH IS 11:42.

38:29.638 --> 38:31.580
I GOT IT!

38:42.521 --> 38:46.425
[ BUTTERFLY BOUCHER'S "NEVER
LEAVE YOUR HEART ALONE" PLAYS ]

38:53.802 --> 38:57.035
Grey: THE EARLY BIRD
CATCHES THE WORM.

38:57.035 --> 38:59.908
A STITCH IN TIME SAVES NINE.

39:01.510 --> 39:02.741
MESSY.

39:02.741 --> 39:04.342
I'M SORRY.

39:04.342 --> 39:06.715
DON'T BE.
YOU SAVED HIS LIFE.

39:06.715 --> 39:09.418
